# domain-models

The domain model consists of several key entities that form the core quest system:

## Quest Structure (Score: 95)
- Quest represents individual quests containing tasks and rewards
- Chapter groups related quests together with shared settings
- ChapterGroup provides top-level organization of chapters
- Dependencies track relationships between quests
- Visibility controls when quests become available
- IconRef/BackgroundRef handle visual representation

## Task System (Score: 90)
- Base Task class defines common task behavior
- Specialized implementations:
  - ItemTask for item collection/crafting goals
  - AdvancementTask for achievement requirements  
  - LocationTask for position-based objectives
- Tasks link to rewards upon completion

## Reward Structure (Score: 85)
- Reward base class for completion bonuses
- Implementations include:
  - ItemReward for item-based rewards
  - XpReward for experience points
  - CommandReward for command execution
  - CustomReward for mod-specific rewards

## Loot System (Score: 90)
- LootTable defines reward probability distributions
- LootPool groups related entries
- LootEntry specifies individual rewards
- LootFunction modifies rewards
- LootCondition controls when rewards are available

## Resource References (Score: 80)
- ItemRef links to game items
- TagRef handles item tag references
- ResourceId provides unique identifiers

